* use Java coding conventions

* do not use abbreviations in names (variables, functions, files, etc.)

* always use braces:
  if(c) {
    then part
  } else {
    else part
  }

* use space between ')' and '{':
  %match(s) {
    p -> { ... }
  }

* do not use space between keyword (if, for, while, etc.) and '(':
  if(test) {
    ...
  }

* use 2 spaces (not tabulation) for indenting

* do not write lines longer than 80 columns. Vi(m) users can add these lines to
  their ~/.vimrc file :
set textwidth=79 "to have an automatic line break
:hi ColorColumn ctermbg=darkgrey "or another color
set colorcolumn=80 "to show a vertical limit

